The paper focuses on the task of bidirectional image retrieval using a combination of convolutional neural networks and multi-layer perceptrons. This task falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of traditional information retrieval approaches, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category, and focuses on image and text matching, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
